5/13/99
  Problems found:
  - The splicing algorithm is WRONG:
      The B pictures after the exit frame are DROPPED!
    Solution:
      Need to keep latest PET of the on channel.  When PET > Tr is found,
      and the new picture's PTS > Tr, then this new picture should be the
      first drop picture after the splice point.

  - Channel clean up:  old method does not work because it cleans up the
      channel before the last pictures are sent out.

    Alternative: instead of deleting vidQue and statQue from beginning
      of the queue, starting from what indicated by muxPicStat.
      This is not easy because we need to calculate number of TPs to delete.
      Not known for the latest PicStat.

    Second alternative: do channel clean up when a channel is reused.
      Ie, do it in spliceControlTask().

    Clean up still cause some trouble.  Postponed.

  - The current PicStat queue size check is only active when the channel
    is ready for switch.  Should we do check also when not ready?

  - With the use of statmux, statQueSz may be much higher.  We need to
    somehow differentiate the PicStat waiting for Mux response, and
    the PicStat waiting for DPI decision!


5/14/99
    The new switcher algorithm seems to run, but has breakups.  It also
    corrupted the pidChansHandle structure in a few minutes and stop accepting
    input.

  Trying to solve the PicStat problems:
    - StatMux skipped picStat
      Detection: picStat from PicStat not at head of statque
      Handling: skip all missing picStat, only output the picStat requested.

    - StatMux too late to response
      Currently ignore this condition

    - Splicer accumulate too many pictures before sending to StatMux
      Detection: need a counter
      Handling: continue bypassing on channel pictures, or dropping off channel
                pictures, until the next splice point is found.

  Changes made:
    - Added counter (spWaitSz) to count picture waiting in splicer.
    - Removed CC correction when talking to statmux.

  No CC problem as shown from the decoder after CC correction removal.
  Timeout count significantly reduced.
  Max wait size in splicer is now limited by the number set.
  Still have picture break up at switch point.


  Channel clean up study:
    Can not clean up a channel right in doSplice() since audio may
    still be coming in!
    Tends to do clean up when channel is reused.

  To do:
    - Use a delay buffer for outChan to smooth out PicStat to statmux
    - check PTS/DTS for I-frame in open and closed GOP cases

  Changes made:
    - forgot to use tsDay in switcher!  Fix by adjusting PTS and DTS
      in bypassOnChanPid().

  Note that sendVideo() send TP's starting from beginning of VidQue!
  If somehow the PicStat's first TP does not start with beginning of VidQue
  then we are in trouble.  This is actually the case we have!

  Seems like above problem happens at the entry picture!

