5/20/99
  Seems that when on channel pic queue overflow, there is no need to advance
  splice time!

  In trySplice(), also check tsDelay.  In case tsDelay is too big, wait for
  next splice opportunity.
  Currently, tsDelay is too big if it is larger than 5 frame time.
  Need to use a more elegant way in the future.

  Problem: with field consistency check, it is possible to get a larger
           tsDelay for on channel.  This means that the on channel is
           in general ahead of the off channel (in adjusted PTS).
           Therefore, the on channel picture queue size limit needs to be
           larger than the off channel picture queue size limit!

  Severe ES problem found!
  Need to verify the operation of off channel pic que overflow clean up.


