5/24/99
  Video server wrap-around problem: The file divi20.m2t starts with a TP
    having PCR and DTS and PTS.  However, the timebase offset is adjust
    right at the wrap around, when the first TP is read, before the last
    picture is the file is past to the Switcher task.

  Solution: Add a tbOffset field in PicStat.  Use the channel tbOffset
    at the first TP of a picture to set this field.


5/25/99
  New code ran for 6 hours.  Then trapped because of bad DTS!
  The bad DTS is due to the DTS wrap around (ffffffff->00000000)

  Problem: muxPicStat not first in statQue in cleanupChan().
  Reason: Forget to clean up remaining pictures before turning off a channel.
          If the next picture comes in right after it is turned off,
          Switcher will drop this picture, advancing the muxPicStat to the
          next picture.  As a result, remaining pictures are stuck in the queue.
  Solution: clean up on channel after the exit anchor unit has been sent out.

  Problem: need to clean up off channel in timeout case, similar to
           above problem!

  Migrate to v3.0 compiler.

  Start using large memory model.
  Need to see whether task switching (taskasm.s60) supports large memory model.


